com.kuka.roboticsAPI.controllerModel.sunrise.execution

Class SprStack

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.kuka.roboticsAPI.controllerModel.sunrise.execution.SprStack
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ISprIdMapping

    public class SprStack
extends Object
implements ISprIdMapping
    Container for a stack of SPRRuntime objects with the following properties:
    • SPRs are added "on top of each other". This must be reflected in the runtime IDs which must be strictly increasing.
    • Removal may happen in any order.
    • To support SPR interconnections, this class implements ISprIdMapping. If two SPRRuntimes corresponding to the same SPR have been added, getRuntimeId(SPR) returns the ID of the most recently added one.
    • If that has been removed, SPR.INVALID_SPR_ID is returned.
    • This class is inherently thread-safe. All methods are synchronized.
    • remove(SPRRuntime) and push(SPRRuntime) invoke Object.notifyAll() on the object, enabling observers to Object.wait() for state changes.
    This element is an undocumented internal feature. It is not intended to be used by applications as it might change or be removed in future versions.
